Alembic migrations for HeySure server.

This directory is the single source of schema truth (see doc/db-migrations.md).
Run all commands from the `server/` directory:

  alembic upgrade head        # apply migrations (uses settings.database_url)
  alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
  alembic check               # fail if models drift from migrations
  alembic downgrade -1        # roll back one revision

env.py resolves the database URL from api.core.settings (or the
ALEMBIC_DATABASE_URL env override) so the same migrations apply to both
SQLite (dev) and Postgres (prod). render_as_batch is enabled for SQLite.
